        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                   Simplify the following without using tables or calculator. 
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <m>sin \,30^\circ \, cos\,45^\circ</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <m>8\,cos\,45^\circ\, sin\,45^\circ </m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <m>sin\,60^\circ\, cos\,45^\circ +sin\,30^\circ\,tan\,45^\circ</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <md>
                                    <mrow>sin \,30^\circ \, cos\,45^\circ=  \amp \frac{1}{2} \times \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} </mrow>
                                    <mrow> =\amp \frac{1}{2\sqrt{2}} </mrow>
                                    
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> 8\,cos\,45^\circ\, sin\,45^\circ=\amp (8\times \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}) \times \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}</mrow>
                                    <mrow> =\amp \frac{8}{\sqrt{2}} \times \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} </mrow>
                                    <mrow> =\amp \frac{8}{\sqrt{2} \times \sqrt{2}} </mrow>
                                    <mrow> =\amp \frac{8}{2} </mrow>
                                    <mrow>= \amp 4</mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <md>
                                    <mrow>sin\,60^\circ\, cos\,45^\circ +sin\,30^\circ\,tan\,45^\circ =\amp  (\frac{\sqrt{3}}{3} \times \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}) +(\frac{1}{2} \times 1)</mrow>
                                    <mrow>= \amp \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2\sqrt{2}} + \frac{1}{2} </mrow>
                                    <mrow> =\amp \frac{\sqrt{3}+ \sqrt{2}}{2\sqrt{2}} </mrow>
                                    
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    The angle at the vertex of a cone is
                    <m>90^\circ</m>. If the slant height is <m>3\sqrt{2\,cm}</m>. Find
                    without using tables:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="(a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                The diameter of the cone
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                The height of the cone.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    Since the vertex angle is <m>90^\circ</m>, the cone can be thought of as half of a right circular cone, meaning that the base of 
                    the cone forms the hypotenuse of a right-angled triangle.
                </p>
                <image width="50%">
                <latex-image label="Triangle20">
                    \begin{tikzpicture}
                         % Define points
                        \coordinate (A) at (0,3); % Apex of the cone
                        \coordinate (B) at (-3,0); % Left base point
                        \coordinate (C) at (3,0); % Right base point
                        \coordinate (D) at (0,0); % Center of the base

                        % Draw the cone
                        \draw[very thick] (A) -- (B) -- (C) -- cycle; % Triangle
                        \draw[dashed,very thick] (A) -- (D); % Height (dashed)

                        % Draw base ellipse
                        \draw[very thick] (-3,0) arc (180:360:3 and 0.8); % Bottom half (dashed)
                        \draw (-3,0) arc (180:0:3 and 0.8); % Top half (solid)

                        % Draw right-angle marker at D
                        \draw (D) ++(-0.3,0) -- ++(0,0.3) -- ++(0.3,0);

                        % Label points
                        \node[above] at (A) {\textbf{A}};
                        \node[left] at (B) {\textbf{B}};
                        \node[right] at (C) {\textbf{C}};
                        \node[below] at (D) {\textbf{D}};
                        % Label slant height
                        \node[left] at (-1.8,1.8) {\(\mathbf{3\sqrt{2}}\)};
                        \node[right] at (1.8,1.8) {\(\mathbf{3\sqrt{2}}\)};
                        
                        % Label height and radius
                        \node[right] at (0,1.5) {\(\mathbf{h}\)};
                        \node[below] at (-1.5,0) {\(\mathbf{r}\)};
                    \end{tikzpicture}
                </latex-image>
                    
                    
                </image>
                <p>
                    Let:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <m>r</m> be the radius of the base,
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <m>h</m> be the height of the cone,
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <m>l=3\sqrt{2\,cm}</m> be the slant height (hypotenuse of the right-angled triangle).
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Since the triangle formed is a right-angled isosceles triangle 
                    (because of the <m>90^\circ</m> vertex angle), we can say:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m>r=h</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Since the right-angled triangle has radius <m>r</m> and height <m>h</m>, we use:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m>r^2=h^2=l^2</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Since <m>r=h</m>, we substitute:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow> r^2+r^2=\amp (3\sqrt{2}) </mrow>
                        <mrow>2r^2= \amp 9 \times 2</mrow>
                        <mrow>r^2= \amp 18 </mrow>
                        <mrow> ^2=\amp 9 </mrow>
                        <mrow> r=\amp 3\,cm</mrow>
                        
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                The diameter of the cone is:
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                Diameter <m>=2r=2(3)=6\,cm</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                The height of the cone;
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                Since <m>h=r</m>, we conclude:
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <m>h=3\,cm</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
        
